name: cred-rea-fish-team-belt-transect-surveys-at-hawaii-island-2005
notes: Belt transects along 3 consecutively-placed, 25m transect lines were surveyed as part of Rapid Ecological Assessments conducted at 19 sites at Hawaii Island in February and March, 2005 from the NOAA vessel Oscar Elton Sette (OES05-02). Raw survey data included species level abundance estimates.
